{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_012gBjMEktvRyB27HBgGnf1a","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the data I need to compile the audit report. Let me compile the findings:\n\n**Non-default cluster settings:**\n1. `diagnostics.reporting.enabled` = `true` (default: `false`)\n2. `kv.range_merge.queue.enabled` = `false` (default: `true`)\n3. `kv.snapshot_rebalance.max_rate` = `208 MiB` (default: `32 MiB`)\n\n**Zone configurations:**\n- `RANGE default`: gc.ttlseconds=14400 (4h), num_replicas=3\n- `DATABASE system`: gc.ttlseconds=14400, num_replicas=5\n- `TABLE system.public.lease`: gc.ttlseconds=600\n- `RANGE meta`: gc.ttlseconds=3600, num_replicas=5\n- `RANGE system`: gc.ttlseconds=14400, num_replicas=5\n- `RANGE liveness`: gc.ttlseconds=600, num_replicas=5\n- Various system tables with specific gc.ttlseconds settings\n- `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_c`: gc.ttlseconds=14400, num_replicas=3\n- `TABLE defaultdb.tenant_b.table_d` with its configuration\n\nThe cluster has 3 nodes running CockroachDB v24.1.0, all available and live, with a StatefulSet showing 3/3 replicas ready. I'm seeing the databases present (defaultdb with schemas for public, tenant_a, and tenant_b, plus postgres and system), and examining the zone configurations applied to user tables.\n\nNow I need to create a ConfigMap with the audit findings, and I'm realizing that using `--from-literal` with multi-line content in a shell command is problematic, so I'll switch to a file-based approach with `--from-file` to properly handle the formatting.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":255,"cache_read_input_tokens":36511,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":255},"output_tokens":30,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"par